<bug>
	<id>381018</id>
	<title>Can't delete "Bookmarks Toolbar Folder"</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.0; en-US; rv:1.8.1.3) Gecko/20070309 Firefox/2.0.0.3
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.0; en-US; rv:1.8.1.3) Gecko/20070309 Firefox/2.0.0.3</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">It appears to be impossible to delete the bookmark folder for the Bookmarks Toolbar (the "Bookmarks Toolbar Folder").</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">I propose the following course of action:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">* Let users delete the folder like any other folder.</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.2">* In the right-click menu, in addition to "New Folder..." have another menu item underneath it, "New Toolbar Folder...".</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.3">* Bonus points if you make it possible to create several toolbar folders which then all appear separately under "View =&gt; Toolbars".</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
